Text: This week started off with our client meeting on Monday.
We met with Hannah and Mimi.

My first thoughts from this meeting is that the scope for this project could be as big or small as we wanted to make it, obviously the clients will be happier with the more that we can provide but we should try and be reasonable about our goals for this project.
It seems from the feedback we have gotten so far that they like the idea's we've come up with and are fairly excited for what is to come.
Throughout this week we have been working on our project proposal.
As part of this we had to do research as well as settle on an idea on how to tackle this project because after our client meeting it was left fairly open as to what we could do.
The first part of the research that we looked into was how other museums integrate technology to increase engagement with their visitors.
The most interesting thing I found in this was that it was common for museums to have user generated content.
They would encourage visitors to create social media posts about their interactions with the exhibits, and this generally seemed to be quite successful.
I also researched NFC tags.
They are fairly cheap to purchase which is nice, but they are also easy to program, as you can just download an app onto your phone that will take care of the process for you.
Although because it was so easy to write to the tags I also decided I should look into the security of them as well.
We don't want people to be able to write over the tags for malicious purposes.
Luckily it seems that you can make them read-only after being programmed.
On Friday we gave our presentation on our project proposal, which we had Hannah and Mimi join us.
I felt our presentation went really well and we received good feedback from them both.
It became apparent that we had more things to think about in regards to this project though.

Like integrating some kind of content management system so that this project could be maintained after we've finished working on it, although I have no experience working with a CMS before so we may not have time to implement it.
It was also pointed out that perhaps we are being too ambitious and we should scale back and focus on a single exhibit at a time which does make sense to approach it that way.
For next week I'd like to have a workable web page design and start coding up the web page.
Some research will need to be done by the team for more technical aspects such as bootstrap and javascript for a more responsive and interactive web page.
We would ideally have the NFC tags ordered next week so they will arrive in time to be implemented for the project.
